Police in Delportshoop, near Kimberley in the Northern Cape, are looking into a case of culpable homicide after a four-vehicle crash on the Delportshoop bridge on Tuesday night. Police spokesperson sergeant Timothy Sam says preliminary investigations indicate that a vehicle driving in the direction of Ulco, tried to overtake a truck but failed to do so due to oncoming traffic.Â This resulted in a case pile-up with two vehicles and the truck. The Barkley West Emergency Services declared 3 persons deceased on the scene whilst 5 passengers were injured and were transported to Barkley West hospital. The road was closed to allow crime scene experts and pathology forensics to clear the scene. Police investigations are continuing. 